FBIS3-9839 "dreeu061_k_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 CROATIA Granic Discusses Issues With Redman LD2903152394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1500 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903152394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Mate Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and minister of foreign affairs, today received the U.S. President's special envoy Charles Redman. Minister Granic and Ambassador Redman had talks about the Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly session and positively assessed developments in the field. They also spoke about specific moves in connection with the implementation of the Washington agreement and the possibility of the Serb side joining the future federation. They stressed it is very important to maintain the current pace of negotiations.
